parameters:
\n<Roselitte>"Originally, we planned to rendezvous with the troops in
Leve and assess the situation before launching an offensive
against Anatos."

\n<Roselitte>"However, Leve is now surrounded by monsters, and the roads
leading there have been cut off... Therefore, we have two
courses of action available to us."

\n<Roselitte>"One, proceed as planned towards Leve, join forces with the
troops, and then launch an offensive against Anatos."

\n<Roselitte>"Currently, soldiers from this region are being summoned to
Leve. Moreover, as a central city, Leve should have
sufficient supplies prepared, so we can expect to secure
enough combat power to oppose the monsters."

\n<Roselitte>"Overcome the monsters besieging Leve, secure ample military
strength, and then launch an offensive. Or wait for
reinforcements from the mainland before counterattacking.
That's one option."

\n<Roselitte>"Two, we alone attack Anatos to rescue Lord Yuri or to
subdue Deorc."

\n<Roselitte>"The most uncertain factor at present is Lord Yuri's safety.
Since he has been taken hostage, we cannot easily attack
even if we have sufficient forces."

\n<Roselitte>"However, if we can manage to rescue Lord Yuri, we can
proceed with our strategy advantageously. It would also make
quelling the situation much easier."

\n<Lyric>"...So you're saying we rescue the crown prince and if
there's a chance, defeat Deorc along the way. Well, we don't
have much time, and it's simple enough. Whether it'll work
out is another matter."

\n<Roselitte>"Head towards Leve to save the city and gain troops, or head
towards Anatos to break the current deadlock. Either way,
it's a dangerous path... I'd like to hear both of your
opinions."

\n<Lyric>"...Yes, Captain. But I have a question. If we're heading
towards Anatos, why is it just us? Why aren't the soldiers
here coming with us?"

\n<Roselitte>"It's not so much that they aren't coming with us; it's more
that it's difficult to bring them along."

\n<Roselitte>"This town seems to be gathering refugees from Abel where
you lived and from other places. Coupled with the damage
from the previous battles, there's a shortage of hands for
even normal security duties."

\n<Roselitte>"Our goal is to rescue Lord Yuri or to subdue Deorc. It's
not a war. Therefore, it's preferable to act swiftly with a
small number of trustworthy companions."

\n<Roselitte>"...I simply trust you more than the soldiers here who
turned their backs on the enemy."

\n<Lyric>"Oh my. You're explaining even though I didn't ask. How
kind~?♪"

\n<Ameria>"Um... Roselitte-san, what do you think we should do? Go to
Leve or head to Anatos?"

\n<Lyric>"My original goal was Begi-Ade anyway. I want to get to
Anatos quickly, and you must have a lot on your mind too, so
I'll follow you.... And besides--"
\n<Lyric>"You want to get to the crown prince quickly, right?"

\n<Lyric>"I think it's fine, really. You should do what you want.
Ameria and I will follow along.... That's okay with you,
right Ameria?"

\n<Ameria>"Yes. Roselitte-san should decide our destination. I'm sure
whatever you decide will be right, and I'll be by your side
until the end."

\n<Lyric>"...Hey Ameria. Was she always this cute? It's kind of
creepy."
\n<Ameria>"It's true, isn't it? Maybe she's a different person..."
\n<Roselitte>"Ah, even Ameria... Will I ever hear the end of this?"

\n<Lyric>"Well, heading to Anatos is fine and all. Whether we're
going to save the crown prince or defeat Deorc, we obviously
can't just march in through the front. What's the plan for
that?"

\n<Lyric>"Huh?... Stop turning into a klutz all of a sudden. I take
back what I said earlier. You haven't thought of anything,
have you?"

\n<Roselitte>"I have been thinking... Ideally, we would infiltrate
inside, but even if we can't, there should be a chance when
Deorc moves again. We'll aim for that and adapt as
necessary."
\n<Lyric>"So it's basically playing it by ear."

\n<Roselitte>"...Ameria. I've heard that Anatos has four gates, one in
each cardinal direction. Do you have any idea if there's
another way in besides those?"
\n<Ameria>"Eh. A way in besides the gates? Hmm..."

\n<Roselitte>"...Well, I suppose it was too much to hope for an easy way
in. It seems we'll have to get close and scout out the
situation--"
\n<Ameria>"--Ah... Maybe there is a way to get inside."
\n<Roselitte>"What did you say? Please, tell me."

\n<Ameria>"That... Can you promise to keep what I'm about to say just
between us?"

\n<Ameria>"...This is something I heard. The lord of Anatos is
connected with thieves, and it seems like they've been
bribing each other."

\n<Roselitte>"Bribes... The lord with thieves? Why on earth would they do
that?"

\n<Ameria>"For smuggling stolen goods and maintaining order around
Anatos. In exchange for not letting them cause trouble
around the town, he buys stolen items from other places."

\n<Ameria>"It allows him to acquire various things at a low price, and
it reduces the cost of security. Plus, if the security is
good, it improves his reputation with the residents and the
imperial homeland, right?"

\n<Ameria>"Anatos strictly manages who comes and goes, so if the lord
were to frequently go outside, it would raise suspicion. So
if he's meeting with thieves, maybe there's a secret passage
or something?"

\n<Roselitte>"Hmm... Well, if that story is true, then there's a
possibility."

\n<Ameria>"Yeah. But it seems like it's true that the lord is
connected with thieves."

\n<Ameria>"...The priest I used to live with. He was demanding hush
money from the lord over this matter..."

With Lyric laughing hysterically in the background,
Roselitte scratched her head and spoke.

\n<Roselitte>"What on earth is that priest thinking... Given his
position, he should report this to the empire immediately."
\n<Ameria>"Um... 'That's how it is in every provincial city'..."
\n<Roselitte>"...You're saying we should pretend we didn't hear this...?"

With tearful eyes looking at her, Roselitte sighed with a
complicated expression.

\n<Roselitte>"...Then perhaps that priest might know of the routes and
places used for bribes. Where is this priest now? Is he in
this town?"

\n<Ameria>"No. When Deorc attacked, he was... coincidentally out. Now
he's in the imperial homeland."
\n<Roselitte>"I see... And you don't know of these places, do you?"

\n<Ameria>"Yes, I'm sorry... But I think probably no one else knows
either. It seems the priest told me secretly for my
knowledge."

\n<Roselitte>"Hmm... However, it's going to be difficult to search
without any clues."

\n<Ameria>"Mm... I'm not sure if it's a good method, but there is a
way to investigate."

\n<Roselitte>"...I see. So you're suggesting we could find out the
locations of the escape routes by questioning the thief
involved in the bribes."

\n<Ameria>"Yes. But I'm sorry, I don't know where that thief is
either."
Roselitte crossed her arms and thought.

\n<Roselitte>"We should be able to track down the thief to some extent by
looking at the investigation records stored in each town.
Tomorrow, let's check the documents in Annabern."

\n<Roselitte>"In addition, we could ask around the townspeople and
refugees about the thief. We might be able to get some
information."

\n<Lyric>"...Alright, it's decided then. So tomorrow we'll gather
information before heading to Anatos, right?"

\n<Roselitte>"Ameria. Lyric. As we continue our journey, we may encounter
even more dangers than before."

\n<Roselitte>"I have no intention of dragging you along against your
will. If you change your mind, please don't hesitate to say
so. I never intended to involve you in the first place...
Understand?"
\n<Ameria>"It's okay. I've already made up my mind."

\n<Lyric>"Nfufu. What about me, I wonder? Maybe I'll change my mind
after sleeping on it... Or rather, let's just go to sleep.
I'm sleepy."
\n<Roselitte>"...Fufu. Yes, perhaps it's time we all got some rest."

\n<Lyric>"...Hm? If you look closely, there are only two places to
sleep."

\n<Roselitte>"There were no rooms available, so I had them put a sofa
instead. You two use the beds."

\n<Lyric>"Ah, no worries. I'll sleep here. I'm used to sleeping in
random places anyway."

\n<Lyric>"Huh? What do you mean 'then'? It's too cramped, so sleep
over there."

\n<Lyric>"...You know, you seem to be getting worse and worse. Can't
even sleep alone inside a room now?"

\n<Ameria>"You might as well give up. Let's just accept it and sleep
together."
Ameria clung to Lyric without waiting for a response.
\n<Lyric>"Hey Roselitte~... Swap with me, I want to sleep alone..."
\n<Lyric>"You know... That guy. The one who appeared before us."
\n<Lyric>"I don't know... But I thought you'd ask more about it."
\n<Roselitte>"...You would tell us if it was something necessary, right?"

\n<Lyric>"Somehow, it feels nostalgic... Ever since I saw his face,
all the time..."

\n<Lyric>"Sleeping together with someone like this, it feels
incredibly nostalgic... That's how it seems to me..."

\n<Lyric>"I have no proof. This is just my imagination. That guy...
no, 'it's' name is--"
And as the night deepened and people fell into silence...
The girl was alone, holding her own body.
